#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.40:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga "
msgstr "4. Situations "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Udāyīsutta "
msgstr "40. With Udāyī "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: udāyī → udāyi (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an4.40:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho udāyī brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho udāyī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Udāyī the brahmin went up to the Buddha, … and asked him, "

msgctxt "an4.40:1.2"
msgid "“bhavampi no gotamo yaññaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti? "
msgstr "“Does Master Gotama praise sacrifice?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.40:1.3"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ yaññaṃ vaṇṇemi; "
msgstr "“Brahmin, I don’t praise all sacrifices. "

msgctxt "an4.40:1.4"
msgid "na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṃ yaññaṃ na vaṇṇemi. "
msgstr "Nor do I criticize all sacrifices. … "

msgctxt "an4.40:1.5"
msgid "Yathārūpe kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe gāvo haññanti, ajeḷakā haññanti, kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti; "
msgstr "Take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of animals are slaughtered. "

msgctxt "an4.40:1.6"
msgid "evarūpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṃ yaññaṃ na vaṇṇemi. "
msgstr "I don’t praise that kind of violent sacrifice. "

msgctxt "an4.40:1.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.40:1.8"
msgid "Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṃ yaññaṃ na upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.40:2.1"
msgid "Yathārūpe ca kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti; "
msgstr "But take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of animals are not slaughtered. "

msgctxt "an4.40:2.2"
msgid "evarūpaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṃ yaññaṃ vaṇṇemi, yadidaṃ niccadānaṃ anukulayaññaṃ. "
msgstr "I do praise that kind of non-violent sacrifice; for example, a regular gift as an ongoing family sacrifice. "

msgctxt "an4.40:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.40:2.4"
msgid "Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṃ yaññaṃ upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.44, sc3
msgctxt "an4.40:3.1"
msgid "Abhisaṅkhataṃ nirārambhaṃ, "
msgstr "The kind of sacrifice that’s allowable and timely, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.2"
msgid "yaññaṃ kālena kappiyaṃ; "
msgstr "well prepared and non-violent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.3"
msgid "Tādisaṃ upasaṃyanti, "
msgstr "is attended by "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:3.4"
msgid "saññatā brahmacārayo. "
msgstr "disciplined spiritual practitioners. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: Vivaṭacchadā → vivattacchadā (bj, pts1) | vivaṭṭacchadā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:4.1"
msgid "Vivaṭacchadā ye loke, "
msgstr "The Buddhas—who have drawn back the veil from the world, "

# NOTE: Accepting BB’s reading of the Pali. But his rendering “transcending destination” is meaningless. “Gati” of course means “place of rebirth”.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:4.2"
msgid "vītivattā kulaṃ gatiṃ; "
msgstr "transcending time and rebirth—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:4.3"
msgid "Yaññametaṃ pasaṃsanti, "
msgstr "praise this sacrifice, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: yaññassa → puññassa (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.40:4.4"
msgid "buddhā yaññassa kovidā. "
msgstr "as they are expert in sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.40:5.1"
msgid "Yaññe vā yadi vā saddhe, "
msgstr "When you’ve prepared a suitable offering, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: habyaṃ → hutaṃ (bj) | huññaṃ (s1-3, km) | bhavyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.40:5.2"
msgid "habyaṃ katvā yathārahaṃ; "
msgstr "whether as sacrifice or for ancestors, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Pasannacitto yajati → pasannacittā yajanti (mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:5.3"
msgid "Pasannacitto yajati, "
msgstr "sacrifice it with confident heart, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:5.4"
msgid "sukhette brahmacārisu. "
msgstr "in the fertile field of spiritual practitioners. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: suppattaṃ → sampattaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:6.1"
msgid "Suhutaṃ suyiṭṭhaṃ suppattaṃ, "
msgstr "When it’s well-gotten, well-offered, and well-sacrificed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:6.2"
msgid "Dakkhiṇeyyesu yaṃ kataṃ; "
msgstr "to those worthy of a religious donation, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:6.3"
msgid "Yañño ca vipulo hoti, "
msgstr "a sacrifice is truly abundant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:6.4"
msgid "Pasīdanti ca devatā. "
msgstr "and even the deities are pleased. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#. VAR: Evaṃ → etaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.40:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ yajitvā medhāvī, "
msgstr "When an intelligent, faithful person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:7.2"
msgid "saddho muttena cetasā; "
msgstr "sacrifices like this, with a mind of letting go, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:7.3"
msgid "Abyābajjhaṃ sukhaṃ lokaṃ, "
msgstr "that astute one is reborn "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:7.4"
msgid "paṇḍito upapajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "in a happy, pleasing world.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.40:7.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.40:7.6"
msgid "Cakkavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an4.40:8.1"
msgid "Cakko saṅgaho sīho, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.2"
msgid "Pasādo vassakārena pañcamaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.3"
msgid "Doṇo aparihāniyo patilīno, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.40:8.4"
msgid "Ujjayo udāyinā te dasāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
